This paper deals with pattern recognition techniques applied to handwritten characters, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of neural networks and minimum edit distance also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of corner detection, which falls under image retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories.
